          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'What are the visiting hours at Kay County Detention Center?',
          acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Kay County Detention Center visiting hours are Monday through Friday 7:30 AM to 9:00 PM, and Saturday and Sunday 7:30 AM to 2:30 PM. Visitors must be at least 18 years old with a valid state-issued ID. Maximum of 2 adults per visit, with visits lasting 30-60 minutes. Call (580) 362-3393 to confirm before visiting.' },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'How long does it take to get released from Kay County Jail?',
          acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'After Angel Bail Bonds posts your bail at the Kay County Detention Center, most defendants are released within 1-4 hours. Processing includes paperwork verification, background checks, property return, and outprocessing. Weekend and holiday releases may take longer due to staffing. We stay in contact until your loved one walks out.' },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'Can I bail someone out of Kay County Jail over the phone?',
          acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes. Angel Bail Bonds handles the entire Kay County bail process remotely – by phone, email, or e-sign. You do not need to visit our office or the jail. We complete paperwork electronically, post bail at the Kay County Detention Center, and keep you updated until release. This is especially helpful for out-of-town family members.' },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'How do I find an inmate in Kay County Jail?',
          acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Search for inmates through the Kay County Sheriff Office website or call the detention center at (580) 362-3393. You can also register with Oklahoma VINE (Victim Information and Notification Everyday) for automatic custody status alerts. If you cannot locate someone, call Angel Bail Bonds at (405) 614-3000 and we will look them up for you free of charge.' },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'How much is bail for a DUI in Kay County, Oklahoma?',
          acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Bail for a first-offense DUI in Kay County is typically $1,000, based on the Oklahoma Uniform Bond Schedule. Second and subsequent DUI offenses carry higher bail amounts set by a judge. With Angel Bail Bonds, you pay a competitive premium rather than the full bail amount. We also offer financing options. Call (405) 614-3000 for a free quote on any Kay County DUI bail bond.' },
        },
      ],
    },
  ],
};
