      <div style="background: white; border-left: 4px solid var(--blue); padding: 20px 24px; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; margin-bottom: 20px;">
        <p style="color: var(--slate-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75;">
          <strong>Kay County is located in north-central Oklahoma along the Kansas border, with a population of approximately 44,000 residents across 920 square miles.</strong> The county seat is Newkirk. Ponca City (pop. ~25,000) is the largest city. Other communities include Blackwell (~7,000), Tonkawa (home to Northern Oklahoma College), Braman, Kaw City, and Nardin. Kay County is approximately 80–90 minutes north of Stillwater via US-177. Angel Bail Bonds serves every community in the county.
        </p>
